Sentencas: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC)-impregnated cathodes are fabricated by the solution infiltration of metal nitrates.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: The effects of complexing agents on the phase structure and the effects of pore formers on the porosity of the scaffold are examined and optimized.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: The thermal expansion behavior, electrical conductivities and electrochemical performance of the cathodes are characterized and optimized.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: A pure perovskite phase is formed after heating at 800 degrees C by adding a relatively small quantity of glycine as the complexing agent.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: Polyvinyl butyral is selected as the pore former for the preparation of porous Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) scaffolds.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient increases slightly from 12.74 x 10(-6) K-1 to 13.28 x 10(-6) K-1 after infiltrating 20 wt% SSC into the SDC scaffold.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: The infiltrated cathode with 20 wt% SSC + 80 wt% SDC shows the electrical conductivity of 15 S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C. A well-connected SSC network is formed in the cathode after infiltrating 20 wt% SSC into the SDC scaffold.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: Cathode polarization resistance values as low as 0.05 Omega cm(2), peak power density values as high as 936 mW cm(-2) and stable performance throughout 325 h of operation at 700 degrees C suggest that the cathodes with the 20 wt% SSC-infiltrated SDC are suitable for practical application.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability

Sentencas: However, for the SSC infiltrated into the 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia scaffold, the interfacial reaction continues to occur during the stability test at 700 degrees C. SDC is preferred as a scaffold for the infiltration of SSC to ensure long-term operational stability.
Titulo: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-infiltrated cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells with improved oxygen reduction activity and stability
